iter                   = Kang Soo-yeon\n| director                 = Kim Young-joon\n| creative_director        = \n| starring                 = {{ubl|[[Suho|Kim Jun-myeon]]|[[Lee Se-young]]}}\n| theme_music_composer     = \n| opentheme                = \n| endtheme                 = \n| composer                 = \n| country                  = {{ubl|South Korea|China}}\n| language                 = Korean\n| num_seasons              = <!-- Increment when new seasons/series begin. See template documentation for more info. -->\n| num_episodes             = 5\n| list_episodes            = \n| executive_producer       = \n| producer                 = Go Dae-hwa\n| editor                   = \n| location                 = <!-- Should be left blank if same as country of origin above.-->\n| cinematography           = \n| camera                   = [[Single camera]]\n| runtime                  = 43\u201346 minutes\n| company                  = {{ubl|SAYON Media|Kwanya Media}}\n| distributor              = Seezn (South Korea)\n| budget                   = \n| network                  = Seezn\n| picture_format           = [[1080i]] ([[HDTV]])\n| audio_format             = [[Dolby Digital]]\n| first_run                = <!-- The nation of which the series first aired. Should be omitted if the same country as country of origin above. -->\n| first_aired              = {{start date|2020|1|17}}\n| last_aired               = {{end date|2020|2|15}}\n| preceded_by              = <!-- Should not be used to indicate a program that preceded another in a television lineup. -->\n| followed_by              = <!-- Should not be used to indicate a program that followed another in a television lineup. -->\n| related                  = <!-- To be used only for remakes, spin-offs, and adaptations -->\n| website                  = \n}}\n\n'''''How Are U Bread''''' ({{Korean|\ud558\uc640\uc720\ube0c\ub808\ub4dc||Hawayubeuredeu}}) is a 2020 South Korean-Chinese web drama starring [[Suho|Kim Jun-myeon]] and [[Lee Se-young]]. The drama will be aired in South Korea (via the [[KT Corporation|KT]]-owned streaming website Seezn) and China simultaneously and is currently in discussion to air in 30 other countries.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=311&aid=0000598309|title=\uc5d1\uc18c \uc218\ud638, \ub4dc\ub77c\ub9c8 '\ud558\uc640\uc720\ube0c\ub808\ub4dc' \ucd9c\uc5f0\u2026\ucc9c\uc7ac \ud30c\ud2f0\uc250 \u5f79|website=entertain.naver.com|access-date=2016-05-09}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://bntnews.hankyung.com/apps/news?popup=0&nkey=201604181001123&c1=04&c2=01&nid=04&mode=sub_view&mode=sub_view|title=\uc5d1\uc18c \uc218\ud638, \ub4dc\ub77c\ub9c8 '\ud558\uc640\uc720\ube0c\ub808\ub4dc' \ucd9c\uc5f0 \ud655\uc815\u2026\ucc9c\uc7ac \ud30c\ud2f0\uc250\ub85c \ubcc0\uc2e0|website=bntnews.hankyung.com|access-date=2016-09-18}}</ref>\n\n==Synopsis==\nA love story between Han Do-woo ([[Suho|Kim Jun-myeon]]) a genius patissier, and Noh Mi-rae ([[Lee Se-young]]) a variety show writer.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://mwave.interest.me/enewsworld/en/article/104564/exos-su-ho-cast-in-drama-how-are-you-bread|title=KPOP NEWS \u2013 EXO\u2032s Su Ho Cast in Drama  'How Are You Bread' {{!}} Mwave|website=mwave.interest.me|access-date=2016-05-11}}</ref>\n\n==Cast==\n===Main===\n*[[Suho|Kim Jun-myeon]] as Han Do-woo<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://kpopherald.koreaherald.com/view.php?ud=201604181037090197592_2|title=EXO Suho to become pastry chef in Chinese-Korean drama|access-date=2016-09-18}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://tenasia.hankyung.com/archives/921224|title={{!}} \uc5d1\uc18c \uc218\ud638, \ub4dc\ub77c\ub9c8 '\ud558\uc640\uc720\ube0c\ub808\ub4dc' \uce90\uc2a4\ud305 \"\u97d3-\u4e2d \ub3d9\uc2dc \ubc29\uc601\"\ud150\uc544\uc2dc\uc544|date=2016-04-18|access-date=2016-09-18}}</ref>\n:A pastry chef, who makes bread that grants people's wishes.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://seoulwave.com/suho-star-new-web-drama-bread/|title=Suho to star in new web drama, 'How Are You Bread' \u2013 Seoulwave|last=Kittyny91|date=2016-04-18|website=Seoulwave|language=en-US|access-date=2016-05-09}}</ref>\n* [[Lee Se-young]] as Noh Mi-rae<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.koogle.tv/media/news/lee-se-young-cast-along-with-exos-suho-for-upcoming-drama-how-are-you-bread/|title=Lee Se Young Cast Along with EXO's Suho for Upcoming Drama 'How Are You Bread'|website=www.koogle.tv|access-date=2016-05-09}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://kpopherald.koreaherald.com/view.php?ud=201604191335306233746_2|title=Lee Se-young to be Suho's girlfriend on 'How Are You Bread'|access-date=2016-09-18}}</ref>\n:A script writer for a variety program that infiltrates the bakery in order to cast Ha Do-woo.\n\n===Supporting===\n* Kang Pil-sun as Damon<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://entertain.naver.com/now/read?oid=213&aid=0000871596|title=\uc5d1\uc18c \uc218\ud638, \ub300\uc5ed \uc5c6\uc774 \uc644\uc131\ud55c \ubca0\uc774\ud0b9 \uacfc\uc815 '\ub208\uae38'|access-date=2017-06-07|language=ko}}</ref>\n* Moon Ji-yoon as Patrick<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://bntnews.hankyung.com/apps/news?popup=0&nkey=201604201414463&c1=04&c2=01&nid=04&mode=sub_view&mode=sub_view|title=\ubb38\uc9c0\uc724-\ud55c\uc18c\uc601-\uac15\ud0dc\ud658, '\ud558\uc640\uc720\ube0c\ub808\ub4dc' \ucd9c\uaca9\u2026\uc5d1\uc18c \uc218\ud638\uc640 \ud638\ud761|website=bntnews.hankyung.com|access-date=2016-09-18}}</ref>\n* Han So-young as Do Do-hae<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://tenasia.hankyung.com/archives/922922|title={{!}} \ud55c\uc18c\uc601, '\ud558\uc640\uc720\ube0c\ub808\ub4dc' \ud569\ub958 \ud655\uc815\u2026\uc5d1\uc18c \uc218\ud638\u00b7\uc774\uc138\uc601\uacfc \ud638\ud761\ud150\uc544\uc2dc\uc544|date=2016-04-20|access-date=2016-09-18}}</ref>\n* [[Sora Jung]] as President Bang<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://bntnews.hankyung.com/apps/news?popup=0&nkey=201604271706183&c1=04&c2=01&nid=04&mode=sub_view&mode=sub_view|title=\uae40\uc11c\ub77c-\uc784\ubcd1\uae30, '\ud558\uc640\uc720\ube0c\ub808\ub4dc' \ud569\ub958\u2026\ud2b9\uae09 \uc870\uc